HEADWORD: Overshoe
<hw>O"ver*shoe`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shoe that is
worn over another for protection from wet or for extra warmth; esp., an
India-rubber shoe; a galosh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

